'''APEC Japan 2010''' was a series of political meetings held around [[Japan]] between the 21 member economies of the [[Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation]] during 2010. It culminated in the 18th APEC Economic Leaders' Meeting held in [[Yokohama]] from November 13–14, 2010.<ref>[http://sankei.jp.msn.com/politics/policy/090325/plc0903251829012-n1.htm 平成22年のAPECは「横浜」で　麻生首相が表明]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} [[MSN]] [[Sankei Shimbun|Sankei News]] 25 March 2009</ref><ref>[http://mainichi.jp/life/money/news/20090722k0000m020046000c.html ＡＰＥＣ：関連会合の日程と開催地を発表　来年秋に開催]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Mainichi.jp 21 July 2009</ref> Japan last hosted an [[APEC]] summit in 1995 in [[Osaka]].<ref>[http://theblackship.com/news/categories/politics/3371-Japan-host-2010-APEC-leaders-meeting-Yokohama.html Japan to host 2010 APEC leaders meeting in Yokohama] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327122324/http://theblackship.com/news/categories/politics/3371-Japan-host-2010-APEC-leaders-meeting-Yokohama.html |date=March 27, 2009 }} [[The Black Ship (news website)|The Black Ship]] 25 March 2009</ref>

A major focus of the meetings were the so-called [[Bogor Goals]], as 2010 was the target year for developed members of the [[Pacific Rim]] to achieve [[free trade]] and investment.{{Citation needed|date=November 2010}}

