The '''Dumpas''' are an [[Indigenous peoples of Oceania|indigenous]] [[ethnic group]] residing in [[Sabah]], eastern [[Malaysia]] on the island of [[Borneo]]. They reside in the kampung Rancangan Nangoh  and Perancangan villages in Labuk-Suguut Subdistrict of [[Sandakan Division]].<ref>{{cite book|author=|title=Journal - Sabah Society, Volume 7|year=1982|publisher=Sabah Society|isbn=|page=57}}</ref> Their [[population]] was estimated at 1,078 in the year 2000. Their language ([[ISO 639-3]] dmv) belongs to the Paitanic branch of the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language family. The language dying out as a result of intermarriage with other groups, and since native speakers also use [[Tambanuo]] in their daily conversation.

